<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kithyen</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-25 08:30:33</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>K here's what I've discovered.  I got lucky and camped Grimrot for 8 hours.  First time his ph spawned up.  210min. prior to this the live version of grimrot had been killed.  Myself, being the level 28 cleric, was sitting hoping for the dead grimrot.  I killed the ph (don't remember what time I killed him).  I waited.  I've heard all these different things like "you have to keep the whole camp alive etc." this part doesn't seem to be true.  Between necros needing bone chips and newbies tearing ass right through the camp not realizing what they are doing I gave up on trying to keep the camp undisturbed and just waited.  210min. after the death of the ph Lord Grimrot spawned and in his skeletal form =).  So in my opinion it's a matter of chance whether or not grimrot spawns depending on time of day or course.  But I can't say that for fact since I got lucky and got him on the second spawn.  Fyi to clerics my level.  He conned yellow to me.  Do not attempt him unless you have lots o mana.  He drained my mana completely and got me down to about 45hp.  The last blast of my undead dd was lucky not to be interrupted otherwise I woulda been grimrot food.  Most should probably wait till about 34 when you get your better Undead DD spell.<BR>
<BR>
-Kithyen<BR>
Level 28 Cleric of Tunare  Saryrn Server.<BR>
